text: I understand why they used CGI. It's not perfect, but it looks good enough. And, no, it's not truly faithful to the book but few movies are ever completely faithful to a 350-page book. Books have much more involved plots, and it's impossible to get all that into a 90-page screenplay. You have to cut a lot of stuff, combine stuff, and there is also the current political climate. What worked well in a novel written almost seventy years ago (a world away) isn't necessarily going to work in our current cultural climate. But the story remains a classic. Even with adaptations. So, overall, it looks like a good movie. I'll definitely see it.
